# internal/server/controller

HTTP controllers (route handlers) for `{{ .Name }}`.

Controllers are responsible for request binding, input validation, calling the service layer, and shaping the HTTP response. Business logic must not live here.

- `health_controller.go` — `GET /healthz` readiness probe

**Convention**: controller structs end with `Controller`; their constructors are `NewXxxController(service XxxService)`.
